    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mechanical tension is the heavy, direct force you place on the muscle fibers, which is a primary driver for muscle hypertrophy. Metabolic stress, on the other hand, is the \"burn\" you feel from the accumulation of metabolites like lactate during high-volume, short-rest sets. Both mechanisms are crucial for growth, but think of tension as the heavy lifting stimulus and metabolic stress as the intense, prolonged effort. Optimizing hypertrophy often involves balancing both elements in your training program.",
      "source": "target",
